<problem id="fs-idm188427552">
<para id="fs-idm241276032">How would the graph in <link target-id="CNX_Chem_09_03_BoylesLaw1"/> change if the number of moles of gas in the sample used to determine the curve were doubled?</para>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-idm181098208">
<para id="fs-idm183267472">The curve would be farther to the right and higher up, but the same basic shape.</para>
</solution>
