<exercise id="fs-idm211017328">
<problem id="fs-idm109304128">
<para id="fs-idm138731120">A spray can is used until it is empty except for the propellant gas, which has a pressure of 1344 torr at 23 °C. If the can is thrown into a fire (T = 475 °C), what will be the pressure in the hot can?</para>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-idm121334432">
<para id="fs-idm234500544">3.40 <m:math><m:mo>×</m:mo></m:math> 10<sup>3</sup> torr</para>
</solution>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-idm244984432">
<problem id="fs-idm220274224">
